HEADWORD: Trisnitrate
<hw>Tris*ni"trate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ thrice
+ E. <ets>nitrate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A nitrate formed
from three molecules of nitric acid; also, less properly, applied to
certain basic nitrates; <as>as, <ex>trisnitrate</ex> of
bismuth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

